WEBVTT

00:01.826 --> 00:03.328
Look with me in your church covenant.

00:06.652 --> 00:21.791
The timing of this message or what we'll get through to it is impeccable because it's our custom at RBC on the first Sunday after Christmas.

00:22.652 --> 00:27.297
To step back from all of our exposition, we've gone verse by verse through 2 Corinthians.

00:29.180 --> 00:31.122
We don't even really go verse by verse.

00:31.266 --> 00:33.670
Like we even preach the punctuation around here.

00:33.690 --> 00:42.503
And what we do the first Sunday after Christmas is we just step back and we get perspective.

00:43.184 --> 00:44.145
What is the mission?

00:44.586 --> 00:45.427
Where are we going?

00:45.768 --> 00:47.070
What are we supposed to be doing?

00:48.331 --> 00:58.066
And so it's the only time all year that I intentionally preach the same sermon on the same Sunday every year, unapologetically.

00:59.906 --> 01:03.171
This time of year, a lot of people are thinking about resolutions.

01:06.236 --> 01:09.941
Resolutions in the new year in many ways have gotten a bad reputation.

01:10.702 --> 01:26.386
And the reason why they've gotten a bad reputation is because you can ask any local gym owner, how many people buy gym memberships for Christmas in the end of the year, and they will tell you that their stock goes out the roof.

01:27.138 --> 01:32.185
Second question, ask them how many people are still in the gym by Valentine's Day.

01:32.746 --> 01:34.528
The answer is almost none.

01:35.810 --> 01:41.779
So when we think about resolutions, we often just don't even give them any attention.

01:43.140 --> 01:55.698
But we see resolutions throughout the Bible, which is why if you'll notice with me in our church covenant, our church covenant is framed according to resolutions

01:55.842 --> 02:01.409
You can accuse this church of many things and believe me, people have and do.

02:01.449 --> 02:07.136
One thing you cannot accuse us of as a church is a lack of clarity.

02:08.297 --> 02:10.139
You know exactly what you're gonna get.

02:10.179 --> 02:22.114
And this starts in our church covenant that we have laid out and you will see the word that I think is a defining word in our life and it is the word resolved.

02:23.375 --> 02:25.618
It's a time to renew our commitments

02:25.794 --> 02:33.965
to triage them to think rightly about the things that really are the most important things in life that give the structure and framework.

02:35.627 --> 02:43.637
One of the greatest examples of faithfulness, I believe, to ever have come from American soil is Jonathan Edwards.

02:44.759 --> 02:48.624
Jonathan Edwards was around 19, maybe 20 years of age.

02:49.045 --> 02:53.170
He lived in the early to mid 1700s.

02:53.250 --> 02:56.475
a brilliant mind at the center of the Great Awakening.

02:56.495 --> 03:03.046
And from the very beginning of his life, he traveled to New York City.

03:03.507 --> 03:10.318
He just finished a master's program at Yale and he found himself in the middle of a church split as a young minister.

03:10.979 --> 03:17.150
And I believe that Edwards at 18 years of age knew quite frankly that he was in over his head.

03:18.352 --> 03:19.794
So he laid out

03:19.906 --> 03:47.506
a series of commitments that framed his life, he was so specific in the way that he would speak to people, the way that he would handle himself in his eating and his drinking, his Bible study and his work life, his thought life, the way that he would forgive others, the way that he would keep himself accountable for the bigger picture and every duty within it.

03:49.058 --> 03:56.305
He begins his resolutions with these words, being sensible that I am unable to do anything without God's help.

03:57.446 --> 04:07.757
I do humbly entreat him by his grace to enable me to keep these resolutions so far as they are agreeable to his will for Christ's sake.

04:08.798 --> 04:17.266
From the very beginning of his life, the motivating factor was that he would direct every aim to the glory of God

04:17.346 --> 04:26.080
He would review these resolutions weekly and he would completely depend on the power of the Holy Spirit consciously in every single one of them.

04:27.181 --> 04:28.043
I want to give you three.

04:29.906 --> 04:43.286
Number five, as a young man, he wrote, resolved never to lose one moment of time, but improve it the most profitable way I possibly can.

04:44.648 --> 04:45.650
I'm guessing

04:45.826 --> 04:52.153
that he didn't spend hours and days on in scrolling Facebook or YouTube videos.

04:54.356 --> 04:57.800
Number 17, resolve that I will live so.

04:57.840 --> 04:59.722
It's my favorite resolution.

05:00.723 --> 05:08.752
Resolve that I will live so as I shall wish I had done when I come to die.

05:10.014 --> 05:13.778
I want to live in such a way right now

05:14.914 --> 05:22.942
that when I come to die, I have very, very few regrets about how I wish I would have lived.

05:24.003 --> 05:34.674
Because when you come to that moment, it's not too late to be saved, but it is a little too late to consider how you've lived your life.

05:36.175 --> 05:42.802
And Edward said, I am gonna use moments right now to set that trajectory

05:43.010 --> 05:47.156
to be as faithful to the master as I possibly can be.

05:48.618 --> 06:03.177
Number 67, and finally, resolved after afflictions to inquire what I am the better for them, what I am the worst for them, and what I have got by them.

06:03.197 --> 06:07.583
Edwards did not have it on a bed of roses.

06:07.824 --> 06:09.586
He was a man of profound suffering.

06:10.818 --> 06:14.122
But have you noticed that it's our suffering that shapes us most?

06:15.905 --> 06:24.376
And Martin Luther said that in trying to destroy him, the devil had made a pretty good Christian out of him, but it was through his suffering.

06:25.658 --> 06:34.029
And God uses that to sanctify us and to bring glory to his son in unspeakable ways.

06:34.169 --> 06:35.090
Doesn't he, Stephanie?

06:37.634 --> 06:48.746
So the title of my sermon, if I ever start it, is the DNA and direction of RBC, new mercies and new opportunities.

06:50.207 --> 06:56.294
We've spent most of the year just hammering out, man, we've worked so hard hammering things out.

06:56.915 --> 06:57.996
Here's what we're gonna do next.

06:58.016 --> 06:59.397
Here's what we're gonna do next.

07:00.038 --> 07:07.506
But I want us to think big picture, because we're not just showing up gathering just to go through the motions every Sunday,

07:07.682 --> 07:23.547
We really do believe that there's a mission and we really are trying to move forward in the mission, both corporately together and then individual in your family and in your life, moving the ball down the field, Lord willing, however he desires.

07:24.709 --> 07:29.356
The illustration that I use often for this is a very vivid one.

07:29.376 --> 07:33.042
How many of you have ever been kayaking or canoeing before?

07:34.690 --> 07:37.635
You know, I don't get in a kayak or canoe with just anyone.

07:37.675 --> 07:42.483
So if we've ever been kayaking before, consider yourself trusted and special.

07:43.725 --> 07:53.381
And the reason is, is because I don't know what it is, but when people get in a kayak or canoe, they just lose their minds.

07:55.444 --> 07:57.347
They have no brains.

07:58.509 --> 08:01.554
If you're on a water in a canoe or a kayak,

08:02.306 --> 08:08.535
I'm telling you, if it stops moving for three seconds, someone in the boat is gonna stand up.

08:09.496 --> 08:12.941
If you have ever done that, will you please raise your hand?

08:12.981 --> 08:19.150
Appreciate the fact that none of you are honest.

08:20.892 --> 08:30.386
What happens as soon as you stand up, and I don't know what you're trying to do, is the boat flips and everyone's wet.

08:31.458 --> 08:39.690
What happens to a lot of families in a lot of churches, ask me how I know, is they don't have a sense of mission.

08:40.471 --> 08:42.714
And so they begin to fight with each other.

08:43.515 --> 08:47.961
They begin to stand up in the canoe and everything is topsy-turvy.

08:49.403 --> 08:54.350
But have you ever regained the sense of that kayak or canoe and begin to paddle?

08:54.811 --> 08:57.234
What's the first thing that happens?

08:57.254 --> 09:00.018
Even the dumbest person in the boat sits down.

09:01.026 --> 09:06.133
And what they do, well, they begin to get on ore and they begin to row.

09:07.495 --> 09:18.409
And you get some momentum, you're convinced that you're going somewhere, you can see the sites and you know there's meaning and purpose and you know that you are going somewhere.

09:18.449 --> 09:22.434
Took a 50 mile kayak trip one time.

09:22.474 --> 09:25.178
There was absolutely no water flow.

09:26.460 --> 09:28.242
You get focused on a mission.

09:29.314 --> 09:35.483
And so what we have done here is to lay out a mission and say it is very clear and we wanna row together.

09:35.903 --> 09:44.195
We do not have time to fight with one another over silly goofy things that will be regretted when you come to die.

09:45.196 --> 09:55.350
The things that we have in common far outweigh as a local church, the things that differentiate us.

09:55.370 --> 09:58.194
And listen, I get it.

09:58.754 --> 10:02.698
And I know and don't give me that serious face.

10:03.559 --> 10:05.561
I know you drive each other crazy.

10:06.302 --> 10:07.123
I know you do.

10:08.325 --> 10:09.586
And I'm going to be honest with you.

10:09.606 --> 10:11.428
You drive me crazy sometimes.

10:12.769 --> 10:13.730
You just do.

10:13.750 --> 10:16.994
And here's the deal.

10:18.696 --> 10:20.598
I drive you crazy sometimes.

10:21.719 --> 10:24.242
And I know you do because I hear about it.

10:27.010 --> 10:29.193
I know you drive each other crazy.

10:30.134 --> 10:31.256
Don't pretend like you don't.

10:33.739 --> 10:42.871
But it's the things that we have in common in the core convictions that ground us together in Jesus Christ.

10:43.151 --> 10:46.576
And it's the core mission that is so clear.

10:47.657 --> 10:50.982
Listen, you know, not just anyone joins this church.

10:51.222 --> 10:54.386
I love it when people come a time or two.

10:54.498 --> 10:58.143
And they almost act like they're doing us a favor because they want to join.

10:58.163 --> 11:01.668
And I'm like, well, I love you, but I don't know.

11:01.688 --> 11:03.290
We'll see if we'll let you join.

11:04.812 --> 11:06.194
I mean, we'll see.

11:07.916 --> 11:20.914
Because, man, we're in the trenches of life together, and I don't want a single person in my canoe that when life gets hard is going to stab me in the back or stab you in the back.

11:21.730 --> 11:24.674
And I want them all out and I want them out immediately.

11:25.255 --> 11:27.599
And as soon as I find out about it, they're gone.

11:29.201 --> 11:35.110
Because we are a family, we have a common set of convictions and we have a mission together.

11:37.493 --> 11:43.262
The only thing that we don't have is we don't have a whole lot of time.

11:45.966 --> 11:48.390
I don't know how much time we have.

11:49.191 --> 11:51.314
I don't know how much time you have.

11:52.034 --> 11:55.177
But I know that we have the time that we have today.

11:55.237 --> 12:03.866
And the only thing that we have in common with our enemy, with hell and with Satan is time.

12:04.907 --> 12:05.367
It's time.

12:08.210 --> 12:10.192
And so let's look at how we are used that.

12:11.333 --> 12:16.038
God birthed this church out of blood, sweat, and tears.

12:16.759 --> 12:20.082
And one of my biggest fears for Reformation Baptist Church

12:20.322 --> 12:22.085
is that we're gonna forget where we come from.

12:22.105 --> 12:39.593
Many of you and I am so overwhelmed and thankful have come since the splits, but you have to hear the stories and you have to know what we were birthed out of because we gave up a lot and we went through hell to start this church.

12:41.155 --> 12:47.826
And hell came against us, but God has been gracious

12:49.282 --> 12:58.953
So look with me in the church covenant as we just begin to walk through that and we'll probably take another Sunday to do so.

13:00.595 --> 13:09.225
What we agreed when we came together from the very beginning was this.

13:10.627 --> 13:13.490
We the members of Reformation Baptist Church

13:14.786 --> 13:35.188
hereby affirm this covenant with one another by God's grace for our good and for God's glory, having been brought, as we believe, by the Spirit of God and divine grace to repent and believe in the Lord Jesus Christ as the Lord's Savior and Supreme Treasurer of our lives.

13:36.189 --> 13:44.658
And upon the profession of our faith, having been baptized in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit,

13:45.346 --> 14:00.689
We do in the presence of God and this assembly solemnly and joyfully covenant with one another as one body in Christ to glorify God by worshiping together and making disciples.

14:01.951 --> 14:02.792
This is who we are.

14:02.812 --> 14:04.094
This is why we exist.

14:04.154 --> 14:05.316
We believe in Christ.

14:05.657 --> 14:06.758
We bear fruit of faith.

14:06.798 --> 14:08.040
We belong to one another.

14:08.441 --> 14:14.450
We give ourselves, as Paul says in 2 Corinthians, first to the Lord and then to one another.

14:15.298 --> 14:16.340
And so we covenant.

14:16.440 --> 14:24.993
It's a binding agreement founded in the eternal covenant of God with the elect, with his children, where he promises to never leave or forsake them.

14:25.333 --> 14:28.718
He promises to pour out all of his covenant blessings upon them.

14:29.099 --> 14:32.183
And he promises to be their God as they're his people.

14:32.584 --> 14:36.069
And this language then describes what we do together.

14:36.390 --> 14:39.274
We picture it through baptism and then through the Lord's Supper.

14:39.755 --> 14:41.938
We explicitly write it out.

14:42.050 --> 14:45.814
through the church covenant, what we already believe is happening through the ordinances.

14:47.296 --> 14:49.398
And so we renewed this regularly.

14:50.099 --> 14:58.408
We are those, if you look with me, the Bible says, are those who have and continue to repent and believe in the Lord Jesus Christ.

14:59.229 --> 15:01.512
He is the King of all the earth in our lives.

15:01.572 --> 15:04.916
He is the Savior and the only one from our sins.

15:04.996 --> 15:06.898
And he is the supreme treasure

15:07.202 --> 15:13.551
to the point in our lives that we would be willing to sell everything we have to buy the field to obtain the treasure.

15:15.254 --> 15:28.573
And it's that profession of faith, beginning with Peter's confession of Christ in Matthew 16, being baptized in the name of the triune God that we come together by covenant under the covenant of God.

15:28.813 --> 15:34.802
And our aim, broadly speaking, is to bring glory to God by worshiping

15:34.914 --> 15:49.291
Together is one which we often do, worshiping in our families, and then help people learn to be conformed to the likeness of Jesus Christ and obey every single thing he said.

15:49.331 --> 15:51.674
That's why we're here.

15:52.975 --> 15:56.379
Most people live and die and they never know their purpose.

15:56.399 --> 15:59.923
And God has freely given it to us every single day.

16:01.025 --> 16:02.226
What are we doing with it?

16:02.562 --> 16:07.971
We lay it out this way, the big picture, the big rocks at RBC.

16:08.672 --> 16:10.855
Our tunnel vision is set on three things.

16:10.895 --> 16:12.398
Number one, the worship of God.

16:13.179 --> 16:16.485
We exist for the worship of God.

16:16.545 --> 16:27.282
Secondly, for the discipleship of one another, to help one another all the way to glory, that his kingdom would come and his rule be done on earth as it is in heaven.

16:28.898 --> 16:35.708
So it's making men and women, boys and girls into disciples of Jesus Christ, lifelong learners and lovers of Him.

16:35.748 --> 16:44.059
Thirdly, it's to be a witness to the world, to be a witness to the transforming power of God to the entire world.

16:45.081 --> 16:57.458
So in our church covenant, we aim in six particular resolutions, beginning number one, we resolve to love Christ supremely.

16:57.730 --> 17:00.094
Number two, to come together regularly.

17:00.454 --> 17:03.078
Number three, to care for one another graciously.

17:03.559 --> 17:05.942
Number four, to serve together faithfully.

17:06.423 --> 17:08.847
Number five, to witness together diligently.

17:08.887 --> 17:11.911
Number six, to walk together righteously.

17:12.673 --> 17:18.401
Turn with me in your Bibles to Matthew chapter 22, verses 37 through 39.

17:18.662 --> 17:26.834
I preach 50, 45,

17:28.130 --> 17:30.353
Expositional sermons a year.

17:31.895 --> 17:33.618
Just go into the next verse.

17:34.419 --> 17:40.508
And you know that because it's taken us an entire year to get through nine chapters of 2 Corinthians.

17:42.230 --> 17:45.135
Welcome to one of my only topical sermons of the year.

17:46.817 --> 17:51.303
Matthew 22 lays out the bullseye so clearly.

17:52.886 --> 17:55.890
This is what we won't regret in the end.

17:56.002 --> 17:59.067
No one ever did this and regretted it.

17:59.467 --> 18:01.350
It's never happened and it never will.

18:02.512 --> 18:12.487
And he said to him in verse 37 of Matthew 22, you shall love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your mind.

18:13.168 --> 18:20.739
This is what the great and first commandment and a second is like it.

18:21.420 --> 18:25.426
You shall love your neighbor as yourself.

18:26.562 --> 18:31.269
Now I get it, that phrase, love your neighbor as yourself has been misused through COVID.

18:31.990 --> 18:39.061
Through all of the, if you don't wear a mask, you're gonna kill your neighbor, just nonsense.

18:39.942 --> 18:48.174
But it is in the Bible, and there is a biblical way to do it, and it is a command and enjoy to love our neighbor the way that we love ourselves.

18:49.676 --> 18:56.146
It begins the Bible said with the aim of the entirety of our lives to love Jesus Christ.

18:57.026 --> 19:15.394
to loosen the grip that we have on so many things in this world and to make sure our grip is first and foremost on Jesus Christ, the one who never changes, the one who is sovereign, the one who is unfailing.

19:16.316 --> 19:23.647
I wanna ask you as we step back 10,000 foot view, we'll get through the weeds through the rest of the year.

19:24.268 --> 19:25.650
Big picture question.

19:25.890 --> 19:29.155
Answer me, answer me honestly and answer me right now.

19:29.736 --> 19:32.961
Is Jesus Christ the crowning treasure of your life?

19:35.164 --> 19:37.287
What do you spend most of your time thinking about?

19:38.389 --> 19:40.192
What do you spend most of your money on?

19:41.534 --> 19:43.938
What are most of your internet searches about?

19:45.079 --> 19:46.762
What does your calendar look like?

19:46.902 --> 19:49.426
What do you talk to your wife mostly about?

19:49.538 --> 19:52.481
What do your kids say come out of your mouth regularly?

19:52.902 --> 19:57.947
What does your life show is the crowning virtue of your life?

19:58.768 --> 20:03.613
Is Jesus Christ the crowning virtue of your life?

20:07.037 --> 20:09.700
There's only one verse that keeps me awake at night.

20:11.602 --> 20:18.770
And it's the verse that says, many will say to me on that day, Lord, we did so many miraculous things.

20:20.386 --> 20:22.769
Listen, I know the right answer to that question.

20:22.809 --> 20:24.230
The right answer is yes.

20:24.451 --> 20:27.074
I've been to church enough to know the answer.

20:28.796 --> 20:38.067
The question is this how we're intending to live and is this what has the vice grip on our life?

20:39.388 --> 20:40.509
It's Jesus Christ.

20:43.553 --> 20:45.395
Seasons come and seasons go.

20:46.657 --> 20:47.858
Children listen to me.

20:49.602 --> 20:50.643
Children listen to me.

20:51.424 --> 20:53.206
You've been so excited about Christmas.

20:54.407 --> 20:58.391
I bet in your mind right now, just sat in your head.

20:58.651 --> 21:00.753
What was one thing you really hoped you got for Christmas?

21:03.215 --> 21:07.019
I bet you in a week you won't know, care, or even remember.

21:08.681 --> 21:12.605
It will be in the junk pile with all of the other things that you wanted so bad.

21:12.645 --> 21:18.130
Adults, it's not just a children's illustration.

21:19.138 --> 21:26.546
What is it that you just set your mind on that has to happen in your life that you have to have in your life?

21:28.528 --> 21:33.674
And then it turns out later, I thank God for unanswered prayers.

21:34.695 --> 21:37.158
That really was not what I needed in my life.

21:37.218 --> 21:40.121
And I spent so much time thinking about that warning that.

21:40.161 --> 21:45.487
Does Jesus Christ have the vice grip on your life?

21:45.567 --> 21:48.050
And do you love him so?

21:48.642 --> 22:06.847
Is he the crowning treasure of your life that you are wanting to direct the entirety of your allegiances, your affections, and your actions towards love God with all of your heart, soul, mind, and strength?

22:08.729 --> 22:09.130
I get it.

22:09.210 --> 22:10.091
It's tough, isn't it?

22:11.813 --> 22:13.796
We're a Reformed church.

22:13.816 --> 22:15.218
It's supposed to be deeper than that.

22:16.898 --> 22:18.680
What does it say in the Greek?

22:18.700 --> 22:20.323
Trace it out in the Old Testament.

22:20.863 --> 22:21.985
Give me some theology.

22:23.026 --> 22:25.149
Your theology means nothing to me without this.

22:28.954 --> 22:34.461
The covenant goes on, look with me in your Bible, and it says to seek God's kingdom.

22:34.522 --> 22:44.895
It's stolen straight from Matthew 16, which says, Jesus taught us to pray, your kingdom come, your will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

22:45.236 --> 22:46.898
We're desiring.

22:47.362 --> 22:54.373
that God would manifest this rule in our lives the same way it's already loved and respected in heaven.

22:55.675 --> 23:04.248
Through the ends of the earth, Matthew 633 says, seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness and all these things will be added to you.

23:05.710 --> 23:11.058
There is not a square inch in all of creation that is off limits to the rule of King Jesus.

23:11.842 --> 23:19.394
And that is why we attempt to speak to every dimension of life because he owns it and he rules it and he has something to say about it.

23:21.777 --> 23:22.979
Look with me in the covenant.

23:23.079 --> 23:23.820
It goes on.

23:24.021 --> 23:26.244
It steals all of this straight from the Bible.

23:26.284 --> 23:29.449
We're just putting it together in a concise summary.

23:29.469 --> 23:31.011
What is the kingdom of God?

23:31.492 --> 23:35.599
It refers to the rule and reign of God, particularly where it's manifested.

23:35.639 --> 23:38.102
It's here because the king has come.

23:38.142 --> 23:40.466
We're seeing his marching orders and his will.

23:40.546 --> 23:47.453
put forth in our lives, but it's not yet because there's still more that He is going to show and manifest.

23:47.894 --> 23:48.975
Look with me in the covenant.

23:49.035 --> 23:53.419
How do we do this through regular devotion to Scripture and prayer?

23:53.840 --> 24:07.794
The London Baptist Confession says, in the first words that open it, the Holy Scriptures are the only sufficient, certain, and infallible standard of all saving, knowledge, faith, and obedience.

24:09.090 --> 24:14.655
Listen to me, I really want to encourage us, and this has been really heavy on my mind over the last few weeks.

24:15.236 --> 24:22.022
I know this may sound so basic, but I found this really something that has to be said.

24:22.042 --> 24:27.407
There's a lot of things that we want to do, Lord willing in the coming year.

24:28.949 --> 24:33.453
Lots of plans in God's grace, Lord willing.

24:33.473 --> 24:36.456
There's books that I want to preach through.

24:36.476 --> 24:38.738
There's ministries that I think

24:38.882 --> 24:47.772
We're gonna engage in, but right now I wanna ask you, is this a reality in your life, regular devotion to scripture and prayer?

24:48.993 --> 24:51.656
You can't get to 10th grade if you haven't passed first grade.

24:51.676 --> 24:56.081
You can't climb to the fourth rung if you've not even put your foot on the first rung.

24:56.782 --> 25:01.907
Are you reading the Bible and praying on a daily basis?

25:02.228 --> 25:04.370
I did not mention devotions.

25:05.058 --> 25:06.680
A few people read more than I do.

25:06.700 --> 25:08.321
I have a whole library full of books.

25:08.381 --> 25:09.903
I'm surrounded by them all the time.

25:09.963 --> 25:10.443
I love them.

25:10.803 --> 25:12.945
But there's only one book that I wear out.

25:13.586 --> 25:19.552
Are you reading the pages of scripture in your life on a regular basis?

25:20.212 --> 25:24.476
Ladies and gentlemen, we can go no farther until that is a reality in our life.

25:24.997 --> 25:26.759
Are we praying every day?

25:27.499 --> 25:34.546
Most of the counseling problems that I spend my life towards, most of them,

25:34.850 --> 25:37.993
or right here, are you reading the Bible and praying every day?

25:38.033 --> 25:40.776
No, no.

25:42.837 --> 25:56.270
I wanna encourage you, whatever that looks like for you, get in the Bible every single day, read it to your soul, read it to your family, and make that a practice that is non-negotiable in your life.

25:56.290 --> 25:59.533
And to pray, if you need some help, guess what?

25:59.793 --> 26:01.355
Look at the church newsletter.

26:01.415 --> 26:04.818
There's a Bible reading plan already laid out there for you.

26:06.114 --> 26:08.797
There's many of them and many people are reading those.

26:10.299 --> 26:14.203
The ordinary means of grace is scripture and it's prayer.

26:14.343 --> 26:20.870
These are the means in our life that God uses to comfort us, to convict us, to direct us, to change us.

26:21.691 --> 26:24.695
This is what we are seeking to establish our church on.

26:25.936 --> 26:32.163
Listen, I've seen lots of videos of what churches have done on Christmas Eve.

26:33.464 --> 26:34.866
Do you watch those videos?

26:35.874 --> 26:41.419
Holy moly, Christmas movies and the pastors.

26:41.980 --> 27:05.362
Listen, if they ever catapult me in here from the ceiling with camels running around and show stars dancing on stage, I'm telling you, if something happens to me and you let that happen in this church, I will beg God to haul every single one of you.

27:06.338 --> 27:09.042
I will beg him until you die.

27:09.062 --> 27:12.747
I will terrorize you if you let that happen."

27:14.409 --> 27:16.512
That is nonsense.

27:17.293 --> 27:18.995
What are we doing?

27:19.055 --> 27:21.859
Why is the mission failing?

27:21.979 --> 27:25.444
It's because churches don't even know what churches are anymore.

27:27.146 --> 27:28.268
What do churches do?

27:28.288 --> 27:33.074
Well, we do a lot of things, but at the heart of it is read the Bible and pray.

27:34.786 --> 27:36.689
We read chapters of Scripture.

27:37.570 --> 27:40.655
We really do believe this stuff.

27:40.675 --> 27:48.607
People who come and visit us may think that it's foolish and they may not believe it, but one thing's for sure, they know we believe it.

27:49.729 --> 27:50.811
We want to pray together.

27:51.111 --> 28:00.786
We want to pray so much and so often that people in our congregation who just pretend to love God but don't really are bored out of their mind.

28:02.882 --> 28:07.749
Look with me in the covenant and to actively fight against our sin.

28:07.809 --> 28:10.614
We're devoted to scripture.

28:10.634 --> 28:11.655
We're devoted to prayer.

28:11.755 --> 28:13.458
We want to know all of scripture.

28:13.478 --> 28:17.504
It's our sword, our bomb, our fire, our hammer, our anchor.

28:17.825 --> 28:19.407
We want to walk through every verse.

28:19.728 --> 28:21.230
We want to obey every command.

28:21.270 --> 28:22.872
We want to trust every promise.

28:23.193 --> 28:26.578
We want to read through every single chapter.

28:27.938 --> 28:33.804
Personally, in our families and in our church, we go verse by verse unapologetically.

28:34.084 --> 28:38.748
You never have to wonder what the sermon's gonna be on next Sunday morning.

28:39.209 --> 28:40.590
Just read the next verse.

28:43.533 --> 28:46.376
And we wanna be a people who see God through prayer.

28:46.496 --> 28:48.257
We wanna be a people of prayer.

28:48.738 --> 28:49.919
What is your prayer life?

28:50.299 --> 28:53.643
Like Jesus said, this is a house of prayer.

28:53.683 --> 28:57.266
And then we have our first mission.

28:57.378 --> 29:00.662
actively fight against our sin.

29:00.682 --> 29:07.291
And that begins with your own sin to put it to death, to mortify it.

29:07.791 --> 29:09.994
There are sins listed throughout the Bible.

29:10.014 --> 29:12.498
There are vise lists of sin.

29:12.538 --> 29:16.703
There are sins that are more distinctly masculine.

29:17.264 --> 29:20.908
Oftentimes, men will struggle more so with certain sins.

29:20.989 --> 29:25.234
There are sins that I have found to be more distinctly feminine

29:25.506 --> 29:44.309
More so women will tend to struggle with some sins, but sin is common to all of us, and all of us to some degree are in violation of the Ten Commandments of God, whatever that expression looks like.

29:44.950 --> 29:51.858
And so one of our missions in life is to fight against our sin and to fight with your own first.

29:52.258 --> 29:56.464
Luther said that all of life should be one of repentance.

29:56.484 --> 29:59.728
Someone says, did you hear about what so-and-so did?

29:59.788 --> 30:08.259
And the answer most of the time is I haven't really thought about it because I got so many sins in my own life that I'm trying to put to death.

30:08.660 --> 30:11.844
I haven't had a whole lot of time to think about putting theirs to death.

30:14.227 --> 30:19.634
And so we want to regularly confess our sins, to side with God against ourselves,

30:19.714 --> 30:27.546
to turn from it and to receive the assurance of God's free pardon and assurance and grace through Jesus Christ.

30:27.566 --> 30:46.034
1 Peter 2, 9 says, but you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for his own possession that you may proclaim the excellencies of him who called you out of darkness and to his marvelous lie.

30:46.274 --> 30:49.919
Listen, once you were not a people, but now you were God's people.

30:50.520 --> 30:54.725
Once you had not received mercy, but now you have received mercy.

30:55.106 --> 31:05.660
Verse 11, beloved, I urge you as sojourners and exiles to abstain from the passions of the flesh which wage war against your soul.

31:06.321 --> 31:12.549
When you wake up in the morning and you wonder who your enemy is, if you are living faithfully, you have many.

31:12.690 --> 31:15.954
And the first one is the person that you see in the mirror.

31:16.962 --> 31:23.952
And so we're fighting against our sin that our sin would be replaced with the fruit of the Holy Spirit and the grace of God.

31:24.012 --> 31:28.219
Look with me secondly in the church covenant.

31:28.239 --> 31:32.986
Number two, we resolve to come together regularly, to come together regularly.

31:34.408 --> 31:35.470
Look with me in the covenant.

31:35.970 --> 31:39.956
Together we resolve to come together regularly for worship.

31:41.138 --> 31:46.546
By the Holy Spirit, we will strive for the unity of this church and knowledge, holiness,

31:47.394 --> 31:54.061
love and peace, and to promote its fruitfulness in the true preaching of the gospel and right use of the ordinances.

31:54.782 --> 32:09.538
We will partake of the Lord's Supper as we remember the past work of Christ on the cross, celebrate the present work of Christ at the Father's right hand, and anticipate the future work of Christ and his return for the full redemption of his bride.

32:09.919 --> 32:13.823
Hebrews 10 says that we're to come together regularly.

32:13.903 --> 32:16.466
It's a normal pattern in our life.

32:17.026 --> 32:24.435
And then we're to urge one another and if I want another, encourage one another to look to the sufficiency of Christ.

32:25.196 --> 32:30.242
Let us one to another Hebrews 10, 19 through 25 says.

32:30.723 --> 32:33.246
It's exactly what we see in Acts chapter two.

32:33.606 --> 32:34.968
They're breaking bread together.

32:35.008 --> 32:36.089
They're meeting together.

32:36.109 --> 32:38.512
You never wondered where they were on the Lord's day.

32:38.812 --> 32:39.974
They were like clockwork.

32:39.994 --> 32:43.378
They were praying, reading the Bible, protecting of the supper,

32:43.970 --> 32:47.315
giving one to another and studying the apostles' teaching.

32:48.577 --> 32:57.129
Look with me in the covenant, by the power of the spirit, we will strive for the unity of this church and knowledge, holiness, love, and peace.

32:58.230 --> 33:06.722
It's the very thing that Jesus prayed for, and it's high priestly prayer, in John 1722, Father, may they be one as we are one.

33:08.405 --> 33:12.210
You know, there's one thing that drives me crazy, and it's when my kids are fighting.

33:13.410 --> 33:16.074
They're trying to kill each other, and I'm ready to kill all of them.

33:17.616 --> 33:18.217
You know what?

33:18.717 --> 33:42.610
Probably drives God crazy when his kids are fighting over silly stuff, which is why he's praying that they would be one as he is one, and that they would strive for the unity of the church so that they would be fighting together in knowledge, to be filled with knowledge, to know the Word of God, to love truth,

33:43.842 --> 33:47.548
tries you made to exploit us riches and you never come to the end of it.

33:48.450 --> 33:55.902
To pursue truth, to love truth, to read scripture, to be informed, and we have done that so much together over the last year.

33:56.302 --> 34:00.850
In holiness, we don't want to walk according to the ways of the Gentiles.

34:01.611 --> 34:02.873
We really want to walk.

34:04.095 --> 34:06.960
God help us the best we can in holiness.

34:08.002 --> 34:10.706
Every single one of us fall away short.

34:11.106 --> 34:14.692
The people around you fall more short of this than you think they do.

34:14.732 --> 34:21.323
The people around you have more struggles in their life than you think they do.

34:23.005 --> 34:25.790
And the reason why I say that is because I know a lot of them.

34:29.075 --> 34:30.618
But we are striving.

34:30.658 --> 34:34.784
The idea is not so much perfection as it is direction.

34:34.844 --> 34:38.290
Yes, Jesus said to be perfect as he is perfect.

34:38.818 --> 34:43.485
And yet we are positionally, but practically we're not, but this is what we're striving for.

34:44.327 --> 34:45.729
None of us have arrived here.

34:46.510 --> 34:47.732
None of us live here.

34:50.236 --> 34:52.480
I said some things this week that I shouldn't have said.

34:52.520 --> 34:58.730
And I'm probably going to say and do some things in the next coming days that I shouldn't do or say.

35:00.813 --> 35:01.414
And you know what?

35:01.514 --> 35:04.018
You have to and you will too.

35:06.722 --> 35:08.264
He said, man, he's so me.

35:08.304 --> 35:09.145
He's so mild.

35:09.165 --> 35:10.127
He holds it together.

35:10.227 --> 35:11.368
Well, let me tell you something.

35:11.809 --> 35:12.871
I got a breaking point.

35:15.755 --> 35:21.783
But what we are seeking to do by the grace of God is to walk in holiness.

35:22.584 --> 35:31.016
My whole point in saying that is to say, nobody around you is there the way that you think they are, but we are striving for it.

35:31.116 --> 35:32.658
We set our aim on it.

35:32.962 --> 35:37.409
We're directing our lives to live in accordance with the character of God.

35:37.469 --> 35:45.420
He says in love, which is the unconditional favor and kindness of God.

35:45.480 --> 36:00.082
He says in peace to truly have the peace of God found in Jesus Christ, we are putting all these things Colossians 3 and Ephesians 4 says, we are putting on these things.

36:01.570 --> 36:06.275
We are constantly in our families, in our personal lives, and in our church doing this.

36:06.896 --> 36:10.100
We are pulling weeds and we are planting seeds.

36:11.201 --> 36:13.383
That's what I'm doing as a dad every single day.

36:13.403 --> 36:17.829
In my heart, with my five children and with this church, there's a weed.

36:18.089 --> 36:19.591
Let's pull it before it grows.

36:20.191 --> 36:24.256
And there is an opportunity to grow some grass.

36:25.978 --> 36:29.682
And what you do, dads, as you pull weeds,

36:30.626 --> 36:36.573
But more so, the focus is not looking for the weeds and snatching them, although that is part of it.

36:37.374 --> 36:48.988
The way that you get healthy soil, the way that you get a healthy culture is you don't go get a lot of pesticides and poison and pollute all of it.

36:49.048 --> 36:54.034
What you do is you plant as much green good grass as you possibly can.

36:55.522 --> 37:04.991
And what you do, Ms. Claudette, and I know because we laid about 22 pallets of it at your house, is you plan it and you plan it and you plan it.

37:05.031 --> 37:12.918
And over time, did any of you go to Ms. Claudette's house the last time we were there?

37:13.579 --> 37:14.860
Some of you did, Jimmy?

37:18.023 --> 37:23.448
Now, I know this may sound kind of crazy, and I might not even be in sermon mode anymore, but let's just think about this.

37:23.468 --> 37:25.490
I want to be honest.

37:26.338 --> 37:28.801
Jimmy, did you know that that grass didn't just show up there?

37:31.344 --> 37:32.125
Did you think about that?

37:32.166 --> 37:33.007
It didn't just happen.

37:34.148 --> 37:36.311
Man, what a, what a pretty view and it is.

37:36.371 --> 37:37.512
God created all of it.

37:38.794 --> 37:40.917
It did show up there, didn't it?

37:40.937 --> 37:43.801
On 22, you ever lay 22 palace of grass?

37:44.962 --> 37:51.090
We got in the truck after we were done and my two sons looked at me

37:51.650 --> 37:54.915
And I'm telling you, they slept better than they've ever slept in their life.

37:55.015 --> 37:56.357
I didn't even recognize them.

37:58.140 --> 38:01.425
They were so tired, they literally couldn't lift their hands.

38:03.187 --> 38:08.796
And they looked at me and they say, Dad, I know what I don't want to do for a living.

38:12.902 --> 38:14.885
And we labored and we labored.

38:14.905 --> 38:19.051
I don't know if you've ever planned a saw on a heel, but I don't recommend it.

38:19.112 --> 38:20.754
I would suggest you pay someone.

38:21.794 --> 38:23.235
which is what Ms. Claudette did.

38:24.937 --> 38:26.098
You did do that, didn't you?

38:26.859 --> 38:27.840
Thanks a lot.

38:29.702 --> 38:33.226
The way that grass got there is it was planted.

38:33.286 --> 38:37.350
Brian, you just got, you got great kids, man.

38:37.370 --> 38:38.551
You just got lucky, didn't you?

38:39.352 --> 38:40.553
You just got lucky, didn't you?

38:41.314 --> 38:42.275
Did you just get lucky?

38:44.277 --> 38:45.358
No, you didn't get lucky.

38:45.398 --> 38:49.362
You're thankful in God's providence that He was more kind than you deserve.

38:49.474 --> 38:52.477
But what you did is you trusted him by his grace.

38:52.877 --> 38:56.981
He did things that you can't do, and then you worked your fingers to the bone.

38:57.161 --> 39:00.505
It doesn't just happen ordinarily.

39:01.606 --> 39:13.878
It comes, the Bible says, through day in and day out, faithful labor, planting good grass, nurturing it and watering it, and praying that God will do it.

39:14.198 --> 39:18.482
Only God can do, which is what we cannot do.

39:18.882 --> 39:19.543
Make it grow.

39:21.705 --> 39:33.340
Knowledge, holiness, love, and peace are four of many seeds and virtues that we want to plan in our life that in a million years you'll never regret.

39:33.380 --> 39:36.123
Is this the aroma of our life?

39:38.506 --> 39:44.133
Is it one of truth and godliness and peace, or is it one that's cranky, critical, and cocky?

39:44.153 --> 39:45.635
What's the aroma of your life?

39:47.097 --> 39:48.018
Baptism

39:48.738 --> 39:57.528
was we come into the new covenant of God and we're identifying with the triune God and he is ministering grace to his children.

39:57.588 --> 40:09.781
As the gospel is on display, the Lord's Supper is we're renewing that covenant with one another and being united more and more to Jesus Christ as our souls are nourished to eternal life.

40:11.203 --> 40:13.685
These are the foundational stones in our life.

40:16.388 --> 40:17.810
For those of you who are

40:18.370 --> 40:21.234
keeping count up only got through page three.

40:21.896 --> 40:23.758
So we'll try fourth or nine next week.

40:27.244 --> 40:35.236
And what I want to do next week is really review the last year in some specific detail, specific passages.

40:36.298 --> 40:40.505
And I want us to look toward what the Lord might do in the coming year.

40:40.545 --> 40:46.514
And then we know the best well laid plans are in the Lord's hands.

40:48.034 --> 40:54.483
but I wanna review his faithfulness next Sunday, and I wanna chart out some opportunities before us.

40:55.825 --> 41:13.190
It starts by loving Christ supremely above all, coming together regularly for worship, scripture and prayer being the center of our lives individually, corporately, and in our families, and then fighting against our own sin.

41:14.451 --> 41:16.274
That will keep you plenty busy.

41:16.898 --> 41:19.581
Kyle, if you do that, you won't have time for much else, will you?

41:21.003 --> 41:22.384
That's gonna keep me pretty busy.

41:23.465 --> 41:26.709
But there's more and we'll come to that in the coming week.

41:27.890 --> 41:31.234
Ultimately, it's not our own efforts of faithfulness that we're trusting.

41:31.314 --> 41:38.462
It's the unmerited efforts of Jesus Christ on our behalf that we trust and that will matter.

41:38.522 --> 41:45.490
And so I urge you, as I urge myself to look to Him, let's pray together.

41:46.402 --> 41:48.525
Father, we thank You that You've given us a mission.

41:49.867 --> 42:01.165
We are as dying men preaching to dying men, but we pray that You would make us strong in grace, and we pray that You would help us to live in every way purposefully.

42:02.547 --> 42:05.732
Lord, help us to be sober minded and reverent.

42:07.555 --> 42:12.402
But Father, it doesn't mean that we live serious all the time like we are in this moment.

42:13.346 --> 42:36.146
Lord, I pray that you would make us into hardened warriors with sharp minds, with steel spines, and yet even as hardened warriors with soft hearts and strong affections for the things that you love and with a holy hatred for the things that you hate.

42:38.722 --> 42:43.510
And Father, we pray that you would make us merry and joyful warriors.

42:44.852 --> 42:58.915
We pray that joy and laughter would permeate our homes and our walls and everything about us because we love you and we trust you and we are pursuing you and you are preserving us.

43:00.137 --> 43:05.586
So Lord, make us merry, joyful warriors.

43:09.730 --> 43:11.217
sorrowful yet rejoicing.

43:13.868 --> 43:16.018
In Jesus' name we pray, Amen.

